5000|$|The United States {{has been}} accused by Amnesty International and other {{international}} human rights organizations of using [...] "extreme isolation and sensory deprivation ... detainees confined to windowless cells ... days without seeing daylight" [...] along with other torture techniques {{with the approval of}} the George W. Bush administration. The organization of <b>European</b> <b>Democratic</b> <b>Lawyers</b> (EDL) has explicitly accused the United States of white torture: [...] "Fundamental rights are violated {{on the part of the}} United States. In Guantánamo prisoners are held under sensory deprivation, ears and eyes covered, hands and feet tied, hands in thick gloves, held in cages without any privacy, always observed, light day and night: This is called white torture." ...|$|E
